  "title": "fix(defer): recover from error",
  "body": "This PR fixes an issue when the deferred function throws an error. The next calls to the function shouldn't be impacted by the error that happens inside a previous call. Previously it was the case because the value of `progress` was reset only if the call to the callback succeeds. It's not the case anymore the value is always reset whether or not the call succeeds.",
